Bill and Denise Richard wrote an op-ed for the Boston Globe about the death penalty for Dzhokhar Tsarnaev . 
  The Richards lost their 8-year-old son Martin at the Boston Marathon finish line on April 15, 2013 . 
  Last week a jury found Tsarnaev guilty on all counts related to the attack . 
  The penalty phase of the trial starts next week and the Richards say they want Tsarnaev to spend the rest of his life in prison . 
  On Tuesday, the Richards marked the two-year anniversary of their son's death . 
  They wrote that Tsarnaev should not be executed because it will prolong the pain of their family . 
 